> If you're craving something that's good and hearty, this recipe has got you covered.
> Pork tenderloin is rubbed with cinnamon and smoked paprika, which brings a layer
> of warm aromatics to the meat. It's then roasted and drizzled in a cherry jam sauce
> that adds sweetness to all that savory. Roasted broccoli on the side adds a fresh
> pop of green, while mashed potatoes keep things creamy and classic.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Place in a #large pot{} with enough
salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep
covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Toss on a
#baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Pork Tenderloin ==

Meanwhile, pat @pork tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; rub with a
large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season generously all over with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Reserve 1⁄4 tsp Cinnamon Paprika Spice (1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings)
in a #small microwave-safe bowl{} for the next step; rub pork all over with
@smoky cinnamon paprika spice{1%tablespoon}.

Place pork on a second baking sheet and roast on middle rack until cooked through,
~{18-20%minutes}.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

== Cherry Sauce ==

To #bowl{} with reserved Cinnamon Paprika Spice, add @cherry jam{2} and
half the @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (save the rest for another use);
stir to combine.

Microwave until warm, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Mash drained potatoes with a #potato masher{} until smooth; stir in scallions,
@sour cream{2%tablespoon}, and @butter{1%tablespoon}. If needed, stir in reserved
potato cooking liquid a splash at a time until potatoes are creamy. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, mashed potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Drizzle sauce over pork
and serve.